Umar Muhammed, Lafia The  Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps in Nasarawa State says  it has apprehended a fake medical  doctor  over the death of a three-year-old  girl, Hauwa. The suspect,  Mudansi Idris,  was allegedly transfusing   blood into Hauwa when a problem developed. The girl was said to have died at the Dalhatu Araf Specialist Hospital, Lafia, following complications from the transfusion. Parading the suspect on Monday in Lafia, the state NSCDC Commandant, Mahmud Fari, said they arrested Idris  after the girl’s  father   reported the incident to the body. According to him,  the suspect was arrested on January  31  along  Sarki Power Street in Lafia, where he runs an unregistered pharmacy and has been practising for over two years. Idris told journalists that he  was  a student of the Collage of Health Technology,  Gboko, and confessed  that he had successfully treated people but not complicated cases like that of the dead girl. Copyright PUNCH.
